headline: Erie Indemnity: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: ERIE, Pa. AP) — Erie Indemnity Co. (ERIE) on Monday reported profit of $63.4 million in its fourth quarter. The Erie, Pennsylvania-based company said it had profit of $1.21 per share.

headline: Erie Indemnity (NASDAQ:ERIE) Misses Q4 CY2025 Revenue Estimates
summary: Insurance management company Erie Indemnity (NASDAQ:ERIE) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025 as sales rose 2.9% year on year to $951 million. Its GAAP profit of $1.21 per share was 23.9% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Erie Indemnity Reports Full Year and Fourth Quarter 2025 Results
summary: Erie Indemnity Company (NASDAQ: ERIE) today announced financial results for the full year and quarter ending December 31, 2025. Net income was $559.3 million, or $10.69 per diluted share, in 2025, compared to $600.3 million, or $11.48 per diluted share, in 2024. Net income was $63.4 million, or $1.21 per diluted share, in the fourth quarter of 2025, compared to $152.0 million, or $2.91 per diluted share, in the fourth quarter of 2024.
